```
This matches our previous calculation.

But earlier, we got `I_{i i} = (3/5) m R²`, but perhaps Lean wants `I_{i i} = (2/5) m R²`. 

But no, perhaps in Lean, `I_{i i}` is defined differently.

Alternatively, perhaps the mistake was in computing `∫ x_i² dx`:

Actually, `∫_{B} x_i² dx = 4 π ∫_{r=0}^R r² r² sin θ dr dθ dφ`?
No, `∫_{B} x_i² dx = ∫_{B} x_i² dx`, and it is easier to integrate in Cartesian coordinates.

Alternatively, we can use the formula for the integral of `x_i²` over a ball in `R^n`:

```
∫_{|x| ≤ R} x_i² dx = (1/n) ∫_{|x| ≤ R} |x|² dx

